Bitcoin Halving #3 (5/2020): Half a year before the event Bitcoin was priced at $7 300 (11/2019). From November 2020 its price soared from $8 700 to $56 600 (10/2021) reaching a historic high of $69 045 on 10/11/2021.

Bitcoin Halving #2 (7/2016): Rewards per block were reduced to 12.5 BTC. Bitcoin's price skyrocketed approximately 9 000% rising from $213 (08/2015) to $19 500 (12/2017). Subsequently Bitcoin entered a downtrend losing over 80% from its peak.

1️⃣ The cryptocurrency market has experienced three Bitcoin Halvings: Bitcoin Halving #1 (11/2012): Rewards per block decreased to 25 BTC. Bitcoin's price surged from $2.29 (11/2011) to $1 114 in early December 2013.
